{
  "stem": "4686.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And food was very scare there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were allowed to send in to each of them daily a little quarter kilogram pack.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Naturally, my father sent it very religiously, every day.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And because we didn't want it to be on the street too much, et cetera-- so there was a boy next door, not a Jewish boy, who everyday took it for-- I don't know-- five [NON-ENGLISH]-- took it every day and posted it.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So it made sure that they, at least, have some food.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And on that day, he didn't felt like it, or something, so my father took the parcel to the post.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And in a half an hour later, people started to tell us that the military police grabbed my father.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Now, not much later, we got a message from one of the uncles what-- that, don't go out on the streets, because they're picking up people from the street.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was too late.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "That was the time that they were deporting the outer parts of Budapest, what's called Kispest, and Ujpest.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And somehow, the numbers didn't fit, or something.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they started to pick up people on the street in Budapest, what never happened before.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "As I mentioned, we were living on the other side of the [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And the military police was stationed there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They were brought up from the country, and they were picking up people.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And they picked up my father in the corner, two houses away from us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "At the same time, same day, they picked up the-- an auntie with her daughter, one of my sister's kindergarten friend, quite a number of people who we knew about.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But all that, we only knew afterwards.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
